    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks. One thing I'm worried about with the corner lot is setbacks and potential encroachments from the sidewalk or neighboring properties. If the building footprint is slightly off or if there's some sort of encroachment on the property lines, how does the city usually handle those violations in an RE-15 zone? Does it disqualify the whole permit?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Zoning violations regarding setbacks or encroachments are usually handled through a formal compliance or enforcement process, not an automatic permit disqualification. If you are planning a structure, the city will require adherence to the established setback lines, and any encroachment would need to be formally addressed, perhaps through a variance application. Minor, unintentional encroachments might be corrected through a compliance notice, but significant issues could require mitigation before approval. Always ensure your plans strictly adhere to the dimensional standards listed for RE-15.",
      "source": "target",
