      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If survey work reveals unauthorized elements like unmapped utilities or informal structures, the zoning review process will likely pause until those issues are resolved. The city often requires the property to be in a legally compliant state before granting a new development permit. You would likely need to address these existing issues—perhaps by getting permits for removal or formalizing their status—before your grocery store application can move forward. It's best to survey the property professionally to identify all existing conditions for the city reviewers.",
